    [ctns_front]
Linear Function<br/>Y-Intercept Form
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
For the $$y$$-intercept $$(0,b)$$ and slope $$m$$, the Y-Intercept Form is given by
$|y = mx + b.|$
    [/ctns_back]
    
    [ctns_backspeak]
For the y-intercept (0 comma b) and the slope m, the Y-Intercept Form is given by the expression

y equals m times x + b
    [/ctns_backspeak]
    

[/ctns_make]
